FromWeb?topicID=11581.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PC on Fungi Covered Great Staff</span><hr size=1> It's self only instaclick, must be equipped.  Sure it stacks with Fungi...but it won't stack with any other regen spell.  And don't forget that it snares you, which might be annoying for a bst.  Goes for about 35k on my server.<br>Is it worth it?  For a pre-58 druid without a quest bp, it isn't bad...I had one for awhile but I didn't really use it after I got a fungi tunic, and once I got a quest bp I just sold it.  I am suspecting that it's best for a bst since they never get any regen spell that powerful.<br>If you have that kind of cash and you 2 box your druid and bst, I'd strongly suggest instead that you spend the money on a quest bp for your druid.  It's the same regen, and a LOT more versatile than that staff. <p><a href="http://www.deadlyvirtues.com/" target="_blank"><img src="http://signature-designs.com/images/shadiza3.jpg" border="0"></a><br><a target="new"href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=42192">Shadiza Silverclaw</a>, Grandmaster<BR><a target="new"href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=188338">Katya Silverpelt</a>, Hierophant<BR>Deadly Virtues ~ Mithaniel Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushad0whands.showPublicProfile?language=EN>shad0whands</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/25/02 9:20:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11581.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> i remember...</span><hr size=1> I remember talking to a 60 shaman about this stick once, he siad there was a way to stack fungi, regrowth and the stick all at once if you have the spell order right or something. dunno maybe he was talking crap but i could of sworn there was a way to make them all stack <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uphreaky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phreaky</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/25/02 9:27:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11581.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.dunko.net/greg/misc/fat.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: i remember...</span><hr size=1> There used to be.  not anymore though.   Because of the snare effect, it used to overwrite SoW if you had it up.   A while back they changed things so that snare and root no longer wipe out sow.  That's when this little sploit stopped working.<br><br>What you'd do is cast sow on yourself, then regrowth.   Click the staff and the effect would overwrite the snare leaving both the click effect and regrowth going.<br><br>To redo the click, simply apply sow first then click away.   This doesn't work any longer though afaik. <p><CENTER><TABLE BORDER="1" CELLPADDING="2"><TR><TD><FONT FACE="MS Sans Serif" SIZE="1"><A TARGET=_ HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4002"><B>Phreaky the Wanderer</B></A><BR><DD><I>Hierophant</I></FONT></TD><TD ROWSPAN="2" VALIGN="CENTER"><FONT FACE="MS Sans Serif" SIZE="1"><A HREF="mailto:phreaky@dunko.net">Email</A></FONT></TD><TD ROWSPAN="2"><FONT FACE="MS Sans Serif" SIZE="1