ey fixed regen stacking I would have Tunic, Chloro and Staff regen on my Troll Shaman that is 40 a tick just there. I could straight up melee Giant Scouts in GD with just slow and my dog melee'ing with me. This is still a awesome tool as I don't have group regrowth. I have one less person to cast Regrowth on and if I need to run I click off staff spell and click epic booties. 30 a tick even after the regen fix is still awesome.<br><br>Kokuei Akujin<br><br>My Shaman Ughlei Duukling<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=179983">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=179983</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushadizasilverclaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shadiza Silverclaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 254<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/25/02 10:39:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11581.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Would shamans keep this after group regen?</span><hr size=1> Yeah, that nerf sucked.  I'm curious Kokuei, would you sell your staff once you get the regrowth of dar khura?  Or do you think it would still be valuable to your shaman?   Am curious about the opinions of any 56+ shaman. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=11581.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showNextMessage?topicID=11581.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11581.topic&index=8><img src=http: